On Sat, 23 Jan 1999, Carsten Gross wrote:
> Perhaps it is only a one liner, but the bttv modules for the Hauppauge
> WinTV are crashing the whole computer 1 or 2 seconds after insmoding
> bttv.o (alt+sysreq+b for reboot works, no log entries). This is true
> for the bttv drivers from xawtv-2.32 as for the ones included in the
> kernel source. 
FWIW, I haven't run into this problem. I'm using an 9808 snapshot of tvset
and the 2.2.0-final bttv module.  I let kmod handle the loading of the
module rather than insmoding it (not that it should make a difference).
This is with a dual P166 on a Tyan Tomcat III and a SMP kernel.
